I created this years ago when I worked at roundtable. You put down chili as your sauce, add some sweet diced onions, put down a little bit if your cheddar cheese, throw half a hot dog down, and cover it in cheese bacon and onions. You lay the hot dogs lengthwise from crust to center of pizza and make sure it's in the middle of each slice. text:
The word fries is not even of American Origin it came from Belgium in WW1 and US soldiers adopted it and shortened it..
Its from French Fries 

The word "fries" in the context of "French fries" comes from the way the potatoes are prepared. The term "fries" is short for "French-fried potatoes," which refers to the method of cooking by deep-frying sliced or julienned potatoes. The "French" in "French fries" refers to the cutting style, as "to French" in culinary terms means to cut food into thin strips, although there's a common misconception that the name indicates the dish originated in France. In fact, French fries likely originated in Belgium, where fried potatoes were popular. The term became widely known after American soldiers stationed in Belgium during World War I were introduced to the dish and called them "French fries," since French was the official language of the Belgian army.

text:
So Wagyu fat actually taste different and have different property than regular beef fat(lower melting temp for one), as such, there is a point to having grounded wagyu products, be it burger or meat ball. That said, it is generally not made with "steak" or high grade cuts, but lesser cuts. Sometimes it is even just wagyu tallow mixed with regular beef.
So it is worth trying, but not if it is at wagyu steak prices.

Also note that "American Wagyu" is a thing, which is a mix breed of angus and wagyu. That taste more like Angus than Wagyu and is not worth the upcharge at all. So at all but the most reputable places, make sure you ask what exactly it is and if they can't or won't say... just don't.

My advice is that if you can, buy some grade 3 or below cut of Wagyu and then maybe some wagyu fat/tallow and make it yourself.
